result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Edward J Fitzgerald was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Edward J Fitzgerald in court with attorney Erik C. Johnson.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states plea agreement.  Defendant to enter plea to Cts 1, 3 & 4.  State will move to dismiss and read-in Cts 2 & 5.  Upon the defendant's plea to Ct 1 and prior to adjudication, defendant will enter into a Deferred Prosecution Agreement for a period of: 24 months with dismissal upon successful completion.  Cts 3 & 4 will request probation with conditions.  Atty Johnson agrees.
Defendant enters No Contest plea to Cts 1, 3 & 4.  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court questions Atty Johnson.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Cts 3 &4.  Court also accepts defendants plea on Ct 1 and approves the 24 month DPA.  Counts 2 & 5 are dismissed and read-in.
State has complied with victim notification requirements.
Counsel make arguments.  Defendant makes statement to the Court.
BY THE COURT:
Ct 1:  24 month DPA approved.

Ct 3:  Sentence withheld, defendant placed on probation for a period of 24 months with the following conditions:  *Serve 90 days in the Marquette County Jail with huber.  Sentence to commence within 60 days.  Granted 3 days credit if revoked. .  *Pay costs of $243.00.  *Pay $100.00 Domestic Abuse Surcharge.  *Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge of $200.00.  *Pay Restitution as ordered in the DPA.  *AODA and comply with any recommendations.  *Counseling as recommended by agent.  *Maintain absolute sobriety as to alcohol and controlled substances.  *Not be on any premises licensed to sell alcohol by the drink.  (No bars or taverns)   *No contact with Lisa Fitzgerald.

Ct 4:  Sentence withheld, defendant placed on probation for a period of 24 months, concurrent to Ct 3 with the following conditions:  *Comply with all conditions in Ct 3.  *Pay costs of $243.00.  *Pay $100.00 Domestic Abuse Surcharge.  

***Bond on file to be applied to restitution first and then to costs.
